                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On September 6, 1953, Prime Minister Ghazi resigned and Prince <persName
                        corresp="#p_DSMK1">Mohammed Daud</persName> formed a new government in which
                    the former Ambassador to the United States, <persName corresp="#p_NSM1">Mohammed
                        Naim</persName>, became the Foreign Minister.</p>
            </div>
